A mi se me olvidó todo el inglés, ella me preguntó que idioma hablas y le dije español ella estaba con su profesora de yoga que es venezolana entonces me entendí con ella y dua se levanto para darme un abrazo, ahí nos tomamos la foto. Les di toda mi atención toda la tarde y cuando se fueron  dua se despidió de mi 😭 y me dejo muy buena propina 😂🥰🩷🩷🩷🩷

text:
I can't help but conclude that aside from the obvious themes of lust and mocking the afterlife "I don't want to live another life" this is blasphemous against Islam. She comes from an Islamic upbringing and background and most certainly understands the significance of dressing in all black and having people run around her counter clockwise in a circle. It seems to be a mocking of the circling of the Kaaba during Hajj.

There is always an esoteric hidden occupy meaning.

Her lust takes her to the edge of a seemingly bottomless pit that she could fall into, but she proclaims it is a simulation and then the camera angle changes and reveals the pit is an illusion and she is not in danger of being cast into any pit for her lust. In short, it is a proclamation that there is no hell and no penalty for lust or fornication.

The entire video and song are basically her covertly renouncing her faith and proclaiming there is no hell, prior to her having her physical followers run a circle around her while she is dressed in black on an elevated platform in a mocking ritual of Hajj, as she proclaims it is all physical. She is set up as an idol on a false altar of sex and orgasm.

Whoever did this video and song has a deep knowledge of the occult and psychological methods of influence with the lyrics and the way the video dance routine was done.
